init_text:
A woman has been dating guy after guy, but it never seems to work out. She’s unaware that she’s actually been dating the same guy over and over; a shapeshifter who’s fallen for her, and is certain he’s going to get it right this time.

One day,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: “I’m not the man I want to be.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: What am I going to do?”

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She was the first person who had given him confidence in a long time.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He didn't need to be a mind reader to know what was going on.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She was right, he wasn't the man she thought he was.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He looked at himself in the mirror again, and he made his decision.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She was looking for a book, and he was looking for her.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And he told her about his plans for the future, and she listened, and seemed to like what he had in mind.
